title: Data limit warning. How can I fix it? What could happen if I ignore it?
content:
I'm getting a data limit warning but can't find anything on what I should do about it.
Do I need to delete anything to create space? If so what sort of things should I delete?
(I just upgraded from pixel 3 to pixel 3XL but that didn't make any difference... I still get the data warning.

Is this okay as is, or do I need to do something about it?
If so, what?

Thanks,
Mark Dorfman
